    • read

      List<Object[]> read(Object... columnsToFetch)
      Executes the query, fetching only values from the given columns. For the purposes of upgrade, this should be used sparingly as it is often slower to process one row at a time than to do one large update/insert/delete query.
      Parameters:
      columnsToFetch - Columns whose values we want. Can be IBeforeUpgradeColumn or String or IBeforeUpgradeColumnRef, or IBeforeUpgradeDBFunction. Passing an empty array implies an already defined select list.
      Returns:
      a List of array of objects, with each array corresponding to a row in the table. The values are returned in the same order as the columns are given.
